author: Pam London
title: Friday’s prep football results
text:
Interlake 48, Mercer Island 41 
Duncan Varela was 19-23 for 224 yards and four touchdowns and carried the ball 22 times for 191 yards and two touchdowns to lead Interlake over Mercer Island in a KingCo 2A/3A game. Varela also rushed for three two-point conversions in the victory.
Sumner 42, Auburn 21 
Connor Wedington had 15 carries for 170 yards and three touchdowns and scored on a 54-yard punt return in Sumner’s SPSL 3A win over Auburn. Luke Ross was 10-11 for 135 yards for the Spartans.

Tahoma 41, Kent-Meridian 35 
Austin Brown had five catches for 169 yards and two touchdowns for Tahoma in an SPSL 4A win over Kent-Meridian. The Bears won it on a 75-yard punt return by Caleb Brown with 1:09 to play in the fourth quarter.
Edmonds-Woodway 33, Shorecrest 6

Tyler Rheinford rushed for 194 yards and three touchdowns for Edmonds-Woodway in a WesCo 3A win over Shorecrest.
King’s 49, South Whidbey 14 
Caleb Perry had six carries for 177 yards and two touchdowns to lead King’s to a Cascade Conference win over South Whidbey. Freshman Joe Green made his first varsity start for the Knights, finishing 5-7 for 62 yards and two touchdowns (one passing, one rushing).
